- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper mentions the document listing problem, which is a common problem in information retrieval. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with set operations and intersections, which are fundamental concepts in discrete mathematics. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed solutions and their time complexity. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the fast set intersection problem can be applied in database systems for efficient query processing.
